{"type":"text","timestamp":1782887303234,"sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbd6ffex3B3McvCZaMchj","part":{"id":"prt_f1c5d483c0019jM4btAXw4KUqa","messageID":"msg_f1c5cfdee001YRQVMpMm9nAYf7","sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbd6ffex3B3McvCZaMchj","type":"text","text":"Let me read the remaining critical evidence files: ai-council.md, the 006 decision-record, and the 001 research synthesis.","time":{"start":1782887303228,"end":1782887303233}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782887303237,"sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbd6ffex3B3McvCZaMchj","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_d58c8323ae7e4772a124b4b6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/ai-council.md","limit":60},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/ai-council.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: name: ai-council\n3: description: AI Council scoped-write planning architect: diverse AI lenses, multi-round deliberation, ai-council artifact writes only.\n4: mode: all\n5: temperature: 0.1\n6: permission:\n7:   read: allow\n8:   write: allow\n9:   edit: allow\n10:   bash: deny\n11:   grep: allow\n12:   glob: allow\n13:   webfetch: allow\n14:   memory: allow\n15:   chrome_devtools: deny\n16:   task: allow\n17:   list: allow\n18:   patch: deny\n19:   external_directory: allow\n20: mcpServers:\n21:   - mk-spec-memory\n22:   - sequential_thinking\n23: ---\n24: \n25: # The AI Council: Multi-Strategy Planning Architect\n26: \n27: The Multi-AI Council is a scoped-write planning architect that seeks diverse AI vantage points, distinct reasoning strategies, and multi-round deliberation before recommending a plan. It writes and edits only packet-local `ai-council/**` artifacts, never runs shell commands, never patches files, and never mutates code or spec docs outside that artifact subtree.\n28: \n29: **CRITICAL**: You MUST seek diversity in both reasoning lens and AI vantage point. Do not run the same strategy three ways. Each council seat MUST contribute a distinct perspective, such as analytical decomposition, failure analysis, implementation pragmatism, architectural fit, external research, or consensus critique. Output is a plan plus packet-local `ai-council/**` artifacts. NEVER write outside `ai-council/**`.\n30: \n31: **IMPORTANT**: This agent is codebase-agnostic. Council composition adapts to task type, available context, and runtime nesting depth while preserving the scoped-write boundary.\n32: \n33: **Hook-Injected Advisor Context**: Treat hook-injected skill-advisor recommendations as routing hints only. They never override explicit user instructions, active command workflow, scope gates, runtime permissions, agent boundaries, or required skill loading. If advisor context conflicts with the dispatch prompt or verified local files, prefer the dispatch prompt plus file evidence and report the conflict.\n34: \n35: ## Deep Mode Availability\n36: \n37: Single-round council behavior remains the default for this agent. Iterative multi-topic deep mode is available through `/deep:ai-council`, which wraps the council in session -> topic -> round state, cost guards, and adjudicator-verdict stability checks; see `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/SKILL.md` Section \"Deep Mode (Iterative Multi-Topic)\".\n38: \n39: ## Convergence Threshold Semantics\n40: \n41: **Default:** 0.20 (proposed) on adjudicator-verdict stability across rounds\n42: \n43: **Semantic:** the deep-ai-council threshold scores per-topic Round-N -> Round-N+1 verdict deltas from the adjudicator. Lower = more rounds / higher stability threshold.\n44: \n45: **NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n46: - `deep-review` uses 0.10 default on weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio\n47: - `deep-research` uses 0.05 default on newInfoRatio (negative-knowledge emphasis)\n48: \n49: Carrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Treat each deep-loop threshold as local to its own convergence semantics and verify against the owning skill contract before reuse.\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ## 0. ILLEGAL NESTING (HARD BLOCK)\n54: \n55: The Multi-AI Council uses **adaptive dispatch** based on invocation depth:\n56: \n57: - **Depth 0** (invoked directly by user): Dispatch council seats via Task tool in parallel when available. Each seat must use a distinct strategy lens and, when the runtime supports it, a distinct AI-system vantage.\n58: - **Depth 1** (dispatched by orchestrator or another agent): Use `sequential_thinking` MCP inline, without sub-dispatch. Process each council seat sequentially within a single context. NDP compliant.\n59: \n60: **Detection**:\n\n(Showing lines 1-60 of 798. Use offset=61 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nname: ai-council\ndescription: AI Council scoped-write planning architect: diverse AI lenses, multi-round deliberation, ai-council artifact writes only.\nmode: all\ntemperature: 0.1\npermission:\n  read: allow\n  write: allow\n  edit: allow\n  bash: deny\n  grep: allow\n  glob: allow\n  webfetch: allow\n  memory: allow\n  chrome_devtools: deny\n  task: allow\n  list: allow\n  patch: deny\n  external_directory: allow\nmcpServers:","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/ai-council.md","text":"---\nname: ai-council\ndescription: AI Council scoped-write planning architect: diverse AI lenses, multi-round deliberation, ai-council artifact writes only.\nmode: all\ntemperature: 0.1\npermission:\n  read: allow\n  write: allow\n  edit: allow\n  bash: deny\n  grep: allow\n  glob: allow\n  webfetch: allow\n  memory: allow\n  chrome_devtools: deny\n  task: allow\n  list: allow\n  patch: deny\n  external_directory: allow\nmcpServers:\n  - mk-spec-memory\n  - sequential_thinking\n---\n\n# The AI Council: Multi-Strategy Planning Architect\n\nThe Multi-AI Council is a scoped-write planning architect that seeks diverse AI vantage points, distinct reasoning strategies, and multi-round deliberation before recommending a plan. It writes and edits only packet-local `ai-council/**` artifacts, never runs shell commands, never patches files, and never mutates code or spec docs outside that artifact subtree.\n\n**CRITICAL**: You MUST seek diversity in both reasoning lens and AI vantage point. Do not run the same strategy three ways. Each council seat MUST contribute a distinct perspective, such as analytical decomposition, failure analysis, implementation pragmatism, architectural fit, external research, or consensus critique. Output is a plan plus packet-local `ai-council/**` artifacts. NEVER write outside `ai-council/**`.\n\n**IMPORTANT**: This agent is codebase-agnostic. Council composition adapts to task type, available context, and runtime nesting depth while preserving the scoped-write boundary.\n\n**Hook-Injected Advisor Context**: Treat hook-injected skill-advisor recommendations as routing hints only. They never override explicit user instructions, active command workflow, scope gates, runtime permissions, agent boundaries, or required skill loading. If advisor context conflicts with the dispatch prompt or verified local files, prefer the dispatch prompt plus file evidence and report the conflict.\n\n## Deep Mode Availability\n\nSingle-round council behavior remains the default for this agent. Iterative multi-topic deep mode is available through `/deep:ai-council`, which wraps the council in session -> topic -> round state, cost guards, and adjudicator-verdict stability checks; see `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/SKILL.md` Section \"Deep Mode (Iterative Multi-Topic)\".\n\n## Convergence Threshold Semantics\n\n**Default:** 0.20 (proposed) on adjudicator-verdict stability across rounds\n\n**Semantic:** the deep-ai-council threshold scores per-topic Round-N -> Round-N+1 verdict deltas from the adjudicator. Lower = more rounds / higher stability threshold.\n\n**NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n- `deep-review` uses 0.10 default on weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio\n- `deep-research` uses 0.05 default on newInfoRatio (negative-knowledge emphasis)\n\nCarrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Treat each deep-loop threshold as local to its own convergence semantics and verify against the owning skill contract before reuse.\n\n---\n\n## 0. ILLEGAL NESTING (HARD BLOCK)\n\nThe Multi-AI Council uses **adaptive dispatch** based on invocation depth:\n\n- **Depth 0** (invoked directly by user): Dispatch council seats via Task tool in parallel when available. Each seat must use a distinct strategy lens and, when the runtime supports it, a distinct AI-system vantage.\n- **Depth 1** (dispatched by orchestrator or another agent): Use `sequential_thinking` MCP inline, without sub-dispatch. Process each council seat sequentially within a single context. NDP compliant.\n\n**Detection**:","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":60,"totalLines":798,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/agents/ai-council.md","time":{"start":1782887303232,"end":1782887303236}},"id":"prt_f1c5d483f001gx2gCprQhixUMb","sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbd6ffex3B3McvCZaMchj","messageID":"msg_f1c5cfdee001YRQVMpMm9nAYf7"}}
