{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782887645532,"sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbd6ffex3B3McvCZaMchj","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_2c82b85a150a4b10a91f3bd2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy - GPT Behavioral Hardening (glm-max lineage)\ndescription: Runtime strategy for the glm-max fan-out lineage tracking GPT behavioral hardening research across KQ1-KQ9.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"gpt behavioral hardening\"\n  - \"ai-council subagent only\"\n  - \"orchestrate hardening v2\"\n  - \"sub-agent enforcement plugin\"\n  - \"gpt vs claude benchmark\"\n  - \"fix-5 unpark decision\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.14.0.19\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy — GPT Behavioral Hardening (glm-max lineage)\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nPersistent research plan for the `glm-max` fan-out lineage. Tracks the 9 key questions (KQ1-KQ9) from `research-prompt.md` across 30 iterations. The stop policy is `max-iterations` (30): convergence before iteration 30 is treated as telemetry only, and the loop broadens its investigative angle rather than synthesizing early.\n\n### Run Contract\n\n- Lineage: `glm-max` (sibling: `gpt-fast-high`). Both target the same spec folder; both run 30 iterations independently.\n- Executor: `cli-opencode` model `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` reasoning `max`.\n- `antiConvergence.minIterations` = 30; `stopPolicy` = `max-iterations`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n\nGPT behavioral hardening follow-up for packet 031: what is still needed to make GPT-backed OpenCode (GPT-5.5 high/fast) reliably invoke and execute deep-loop workflows the way Claude does — correctly, promptly, without getting stuck on pre-defined flows or over-literal misreads. Covers ai-council subagent-only conversion, `@orchestrate` hardening v2, a sub-agent-enforcement plugin, a GPT-vs-Claude behavioral benchmark, and the FIX-5 unpark decision.\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n\n- [ ] **KQ1** — Decisive smoke evidence: design a genuinely external (non-OpenCode-shell) run of all 4 command-owned deep-mode smokes precise enough to yield a clean PASS/FAIL.\n- [ ] **KQ2** — Real-world mis-route mechanism: classify the operator's symptom set (slow orchestrate, wrong sub-agent, stuck flows, overthinking) — same modes A/B/C, a new mode, or a latency/UX issue.\n- [ ] **KQ3** — `ai-council` subagent-only conversion: should `mode: all` → subagent-only; what breaks; safest migration; deep.md/orchestrate.md co-dependencies.\n- [ ] **KQ4** — `@orchestrate` hardening v2: delegate deep-dispatch entirely to `deep.md` (single routing truth) instead of the judgment-dependent Deep Route field.\n- [ ] **KQ5** — Sub-agent-enforcement plugin: feasibility of a hook-based plugin structurally forcing correct sub-agent selection; mechanism and home; scope vs phase 006/FIX-5.\n- [ ] **KQ6** — GPT-vs-Claude behavioral benchmark: minimal repeatable benchmark (latency + first-dispatch correctness across 4 modes), baseline + regression gate.\n- [ ] **KQ7** — Literal-instruction-following pattern: extract the generalizable pattern that makes `deep.md` literal-model-safe; identify adopters.\n- [ ] **KQ8** — Propagation scope: enumerate which other commands/skills need the same hardening (file paths).\n- [ ] **KQ9** — FIX-5 unpark decision: a clear decision criterion distinct from phase 006's inconclusive trigger; unpark now / wait on KQ1 / neither.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n\n- Do NOT implement code in this research pass; produce a design + evidence-backed recommendations.\n- Do NOT re-derive the original mis-route root-cause taxonomy (modes A/B/C) or route-proof validator mechanics — already established in phase 001 research and implemented in phase 002.\n- Do NOT treat \"phases 002-004 are complete\" as sufficient without addressing why phase 005 never reached a real leaf dispatch.\n- Do NOT over-constrain Claude — preserve its existing flexibility while hardening for GPT.\n\n---\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n\n- **Primary stop:** iteration count reaches `maxIterations` (30). Convergence signals before iteration 30 are telemetry only.\n- On any coverage/quality plateau before iteration 30: actively change investigative angle (different KQ, different evidence source, adversarial re-check of an earlier conclusion) rather than stopping.\n- Final synthesis only after 30 iterations AND all of KQ1-KQ9 have evidence-backed answers with `file:line` citations.\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n\n[None yet — populated as iterations answer KQs]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n\n[First iteration — populated after iteration 1 completes]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n\n[First iteration — populated after iteration 1 completes]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n\n[Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n\n[Consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n\n[Populated after iteration 1 completes]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n\nIteration 1: Establish the evidence inventory — read the predecessor research, the 005/006 phase docs, and the deep.md/orchestrate.md/ai-council.md files to lock down citation handles before any analysis.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n\n- **Predecessor research (root cause, CONFIRMED):** `subagent_type` is normalized to `\"general\"` for every custom-agent dispatch — specialized identity is only prompt-injected, never runtime-enforced (soft identity boundary). `../001-deep-agent-router-and-orchestration/research/research.md` §1.\n- **Phases 002-004** (route-proof validation, `deep.md` primary router, `orchestrate.md` Deep Route field, pre-route headers): code-complete and independently re-verified.\n- **Phase 005** (GPT verification smoke, the acceptance gate): **inconclusive** — 0/4 command-owned smokes reached a real leaf dispatch; all blocked upstream by `cli-opencode` self-invocation guards. The one decisive path (rerun the smoke from a genuine external, non-OpenCode shell) was never taken.\n- **Phase 006 / FIX-5** (host hard identity): stays **Parked** on the inconclusive 005 evidence, not on proof the agent-layer fix works. `../006-host-hard-identity-fix5/decision-record.md`.\n- **`deep.md`**: `mode: primary`, deterministic table lookup, 8-step routing workflow with only one judgment call (a single clarification question) — materially more literal-model-safe than orchestrate's Deep Route field.\n- **`ai-council.md`**: currently `mode: all` (directly invocable in OpenCode), NOT subagent-only.\n- **Operator symptom report (2026-07-01, real-world usage):** GPT is very slow as `@orchestrate` primary; frequently fails to invoke the correct deep sub-agent; gets stuck on pre-defined flows (deep-loop commands especially); overthinks and needs literal, deterministic instructions.\n- **resource-map.md:** NOT present in this spec folder; skipping the coverage gate.\n\n---\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n\n- Max iterations: 30\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05 (telemetry only; stop policy = max-iterations)\n- Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n- Progressive synthesis: true (default)\n- `research.md` ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output (lineage-scoped)\n- Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred)\n- Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11A\n- Current generation: 1\n- Started: 2026-07-01T06:22:49.753Z\n","filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/007-gpt-behavioral-hardening-research/research/lineages/glm-max/deep-research-strategy.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/007-gpt-behavioral-hardening-research/research/lineages/glm-max/deep-research-strategy.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/007-gpt-behavioral-hardening-research/research/lineages/glm-max/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1782887645528,"end":1782887645531}},"id":"prt_f1c628156001GYHpLI6Avkt492","sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbd6ffex3B3McvCZaMchj","messageID":"msg_f1c61bcce001IbgnVVBh1B2D7Q"}}
