{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782887726868,"sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbd6ffex3B3McvCZaMchj","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_2b654a7bcd6a45eca8a8b435","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"cd \"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public\" && echo \"=== self-invocation guard (OPENCODE_PID) ===\"; rg -rn \"OPENCODE_PID|self.invocation|self_invocation|nested.*opencode|refused from inside\" .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/ 2>/dev/null | head -15; echo \"\"; echo \"=== mk-goal plugin / injection pattern (032) ===\"; rg -rln \"mk-goal|injection.plugin|hook.*inject|goal.*inject\" .opencode/specs/ 2>/dev/null | head -10; echo \"\"; echo \"=== orchestrate Deep Route Priority table ===\"; rg -n \"Deep Route|Priority|deep-context|deep-review\" .opencode/agents/orchestrate.md | head -20"},"output":"...output truncated...\n\nFull output saved to: /Users/michelkerkmeester/.local/share/opencode/tool-output/tool_f1c63bf02001LdLiNirEJQJPzL\n\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/002-sk-deep-research-refinement/research/iterations/iteration-009.md:  - **Relevance to sk-deep-research**: Our system relies on the agent reading state files (Step 1 of workflow). A context ln could eliminate the need for explicit state-reading tool calls, saving 2 tool calls per iteration. However, this approach is runtime-specific (requires plugin/extension support) and would not work across all 4 runtimes.\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/002-sk-deep-research-refinement/research/iterations/iteration-009.md:**Honest assessment**: This iteration is primarily consolidation. The genuinely new information is: (a) the autoresearch-opencode context ln pattern, (b) identification of tool call budget and breakthrough detection as gaps not covered by v3 proposals, (c) the WIRE/EXTEND/PROTECT categorization. Most work confirmed existing findings.\n.opencode/specs/design/003-mcp-figma-with-direct-cli-support/review/session-audit/lineages/deepseek-v4-pro/logs/fanout-lineage.out:{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1781459155276,\"sessionID\":\"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_00_LIDc0iSFcj2x5yd4lZdU3821\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Deep Review Loop Protocol\\n3: description: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop, initialization, iteration, convergence, synthesis, and save phases.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"deep review loop protocol\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"review iteration lifecycle\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"review loop initialization\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"review auto resume\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"review synthesis phase\\\"\\n10: importance_tier: important\\n11: contextType: implementation\\n12: ---\\n13: \\n14: # Deep Review Loop Protocol\\n15: \\n16: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop.\\n17: \\n18: ---\\n19: \\n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n21: \\n22: ### Purpose\\n23: \\n24: The deep review loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save. The YAML workflow manages the lifecycle. The `@deep-review` agent (LEAF-only, no WebFetch) executes individual review iterations with fresh context each time.\\n25: \\n26: ### When to Use\\n27: \\n28: - Initiating a deep-review loop on a spec folder, skill, agent, or track.\\n29: - Resuming a paused or interrupted review session from prior state.\\n30: - Validating the 4-phase lifecycle and lineage protocol against current behavior.\\n31: - Auditing iteration-dispatch, convergence, or save-phase contracts before changes.\\n32: \\n33: ```\\n34: ┌──────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\\n35: │  INIT        │────>│  LOOP                         │────>│  SYNTHESIS    │────>│  SAVE    │\\n36: │              │     │  ┌─────────────────────────┐  │     │               │     │          │\\n37: │ Scope        │     │  │ Read State              │  │     │ Finding       │     │ Memory   │\\n38: │ Discovery    │     │  │ Check Convergence       │  │     │ Registry      │     │ Context  │\\n39: │ Dimension    │     │  │ Check Pause Sentinel    │  │     │ Dedup         │     │ Save     │\\n40: │ Ordering     │     │  │ Generate State Summary  │  │     │               │     │          │\\n41: │ Traceability │     │  │ Dispatch @deep-review   │  │     │ Severity      │     │          │\\n42: │ Planning     │     │  │ Evaluate Results        │  │     │ Reconcile     │     │          │\\n43: │ State Files  │     │  │ Claim Adjudication      │  │     │               │     │          │\\n44: │              │     │  │ Dashboard Generation    │  │     │ Replay        │     │          │\\n45: │              │     │  │ Loop Decision           │  │     │ Validation    │     │          │\\n46: │              │     │  └────────┬────────────────┘  │     │               │     │          │\\n47: │              │     │           │ repeat            │     │ review-report │     │          │\\n48: │              │     │           │                   │     │ (9 core +     │     │          │\\n49: │              │     │           │                   │     │  resource-map)│     │          │\\n50: └──────────────┘     └───────────────────────────────┘     └───────────────┘     └──────────┘\\n51: ```\\n52: \\n53: ### Core Innovation\\n54: \\n55: Each agent dispatch gets a fresh context window. State continuity comes from files on disk, not in-context memory. This eliminates context degradation in long review sessions where accumulated findings would otherwise bias subsequent dimensions.\\n56: \\n57: ### Key References\\n58: \\n59: | Resource | Path | Purpose |\\n60: |----------|------|---------|\\n61: | Review contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\\n62: | Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_auto.yaml` | Unattended review loop |\\n63: | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_confirm.yaml` | Step-by-step review with approval gates |\\n64: | Agent | `@deep-review` (LEAF) | Single iteration executor, no sub-agents, no WebFetch |\\n65: | Memory save | `generate-context.js` | Context preservation script |\\n66: \\n67: ---\\n68: \\n69: ## 2. PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\\n70: \\n71: ### Purpose\\n72: \\n73: Set up all state files for a new review session. Discover the scope, order dimensions by risk priority, establish the traceability protocol plan, and create the review state packet.\\n74: \\n75: ### Steps\\n76: \\n77: 1. **Classify session state before writing**:\\n78:    - `fresh`: no config/state/strategy files exist\\n79:    - `resume`: config + state + strategy all exist and agree\\n80:    - `completed-session`: consistent prior state with `config.status == \\\"complete\\\"`\\n81:    - `invalid-state`: partial or contradictory artifacts\\n82: \\n83: 2. **Resolve local artifact owner**: `artifact_dir = resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review').artifactDir`, then `mkdir -p {artifact_dir}/iterations`\\n84: \\n85: 3. **Scope discovery**: Resolve the review target into a concrete file list using one of 5 target types:\\n86: \\n87:    | Target Type | CLI Value | Resolution Strategy |\\n88:    |-------------|-----------|---------------------|\\n89:    | **Spec Folder** | `spec-folder` | Read `spec.md`, `plan.md`, implementation files listed in `tasks.md` |\\n90:    | **Skill** | `skill` | Read `SKILL.md`, `references/`, `assets/`, `scripts/`, find agent definitions and command entry points |\\n91:    | **Agent** | `agent` | Find agent definitions across all runtimes, compare for consistency |\\n92:    | **Track** | `track` | List all child spec folders under the track, read `spec.md` + `checklist.md` for each |\\n93:    | **Files** | `files` | Expand glob patterns, validate existence, discover cross-references |\\n94: \\n95:    Store the resolved file list in strategy.md \\\"Files Under Review\\\".\\n96: \\n97: 4. **Dimension ordering**: Order the 4 review dimensions for iteration based on risk priority:\\n98: \\n99:    | Priority | Dimension | Rationale |\\n100:    |----------|-----------|-----------|\\n101:    | 1 | Correctness | Logic errors have the highest blast radius |\\n102:    | 2 | Security | Vulnerabilities require immediate attention |\\n103:    | 3 | Traceability | Spec/code alignment ensures completeness |\\n104:    | 4 | Maintainability | Patterns and documentation quality (lowest immediate risk) |\\n105: \\n106:    Default order: D1 Correctness, D2 Security, D3 Traceability, D4 Maintainability. This order is configurable but the default prioritizes highest-impact dimensions first.\\n107: \\n108: 5. **Traceability protocol planning**: Partition the 6 cross-reference protocols into core vs overlay, and schedule only applicable overlays for the target type:\\n109: \\n110:    | Level | Protocol | Applies To | Gate Class | Purpose |\\n111:    |-------|----------|------------|------------|---------|\\n112:    | Core | `spec_code` | all targets | hard | Verify normative claims resolve to shipped behavior |\\n113:    | Core | `checklist_evidence` | all targets | hard | Verify checked completion claims have evidence |\\n114:    | Overlay | `skill_agent` | skill | advisory | Verify SKILL.md and runtime agents agree |\\n115:    | Overlay | `agent_cross_runtime` | agent | advisory | Verify runtime agent parity |\\n116:    | Overlay | `feature_catalog_code` | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory | Verify catalog claims match capability |\\n117:    | Overlay | `playbook_capability` | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory | Verify playbook scenarios match executable reality |\\n118: \\n119:    Only schedule overlay protocols that apply to the resolved target type.\\n120: \\n121: 6. **Write config**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` with `mode: \\\"review\\\"`, lineage metadata (`sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`), and review-specific fields including target, target type, dimensions, protocol plan, and release-readiness state.\\n122: \\n123: 7. **Initialize state log**: First line of `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` with config record including `mode: \\\"review\\\"` and the lineage fields.\\n124: \\n125: 8. **Initialize reducer state**: Create `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` with empty `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `repeatedFindings`, `dimensionCoverage`, `findingsBySeverity`, and `convergenceScore`.\\n126: \\n127: 9. **Initialize strategy**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` from review template with:\\n128:    - Topic (review target description)\\n129:    - Review Dimensions checklist\\n130:    - Files Under Review table\\n131:    - Cross-Reference Status table grouped by core vs overlay\\n132:    - Known Context from `memory_context()` results (if any)\\n133:    - Resource-map snapshot when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init\\n134:    - `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate` when it does not\\n135:    - Review Boundaries from config\\n136: 9a. **Initialize resource-map coverage state**:\\n137:    - If `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init: set `resource_map_present = true`, add `Resource Map Coverage` to the Review Charter, and persist a concise map summary in `Known Context`\\n138:    - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false`, record the skip note in `Known Context`, and continue without failing\\n139: \\n140: 10. **Validate review charter**:\\n141:    - Verify strategy.md contains Non-Goals and Stop Conditions sections (may be empty but must exist)\\n142:    - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (target, dimensions, scope, non-lned as the agent's context (native) or piped to `codex exec` stdin (cli-codex). Config is in `assets/deep_review_config.json` under the `executor` key; schema in `deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. CLI flag precedence: `--executor/--model/--reasoning-effort/--service-tier/--executor-timeout > config file > schema default`.\\n\\n### What Never Changes Regardless Of Executor Route\\n\\n- YAML owns state (`deep-review-state.jsonl`, strategy.md, registry, dashboard).\\n- `reduce-state.cjs` is the single state writer.\\n- Convergence detection, lifecycle events (new/resume/restart), the review dimensions pass, and stuck_recovery stay YAML-driven.\\n- The `@deep-review` LEAF agent definition is untouched: it is the native executor, not the only one.\\n\\n### Code-Graph Readiness TrustState Surface\\n\\nOn this skill surface, the live code-graph readiness contract only reaches four TrustState values: `live`, `stale`, `absent`, and `unavailable`. The values `cached`, `imported`, `rebuilt`, and `rehomed` remain declared in the shared TrustState type for compatibility and downstream schema stability, but the seven code-graph handlers and readiness helpers used here do not emit them today.\",\"lineStart\":1,\"lineEnd\":765,\"totalLines\":765,\"truncated\":false}},\"title\":\".opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\"time\":{\"start\":1781459155270,\"end\":1781459155275}},\"id\":\"prt_ec73d77b500180G4xPo5Ne6ogW\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ\",\"messageID\":\"msg_ec73d6127001esGof6gVcWcEiv\"}}\n.opencode/specs/design/002-mcp-open-design/review/session-audit/lineages/mimo-v25-pro/logs/fanout-lineage.out:{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1781458394776,\"sessionID\":\"ses_138ce4b78ffe7H1eTmRgkr1Vek\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_0935d030a4c54d98b6b953bd\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Deep Review Loop Protocol\\n3: description: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop, initialization, iteration, convergence, synthesis, and save phases.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"deep review loop protocol\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"review iteration lifecycle\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"review loop initialization\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"review auto resume\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"review synthesis phase\\\"\\n10: importance_tier: important\\n11: contextType: implementation\\n12: ---\\n13: \\n14: # Deep Review Loop Protocol\\n15: \\n16: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop.\\n17: \\n18: ---\\n19: \\n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n21: \\n22: ### Purpose\\n23: \\n24: The deep review loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save. The YAML workflow manages the lifecycle. The `@deep-review` agent (LEAF-only, no WebFetch) executes individual review iterations with fresh context each time.\\n25: \\n26: ### When to Use\\n27: \\n28: - Initiating a deep-review loop on a spec folder, skill, agent, or track.\\n29: - Resuming a paused or interrupted review session from prior state.\\n30: - Validating the 4-phase lifecycle and lineage protocol against current behavior.\\n31: - Auditing iteration-dispatch, convergence, or save-phase contracts before changes.\\n32: \\n33: ```\\n34: ┌──────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\\n35: │  INIT        │────>│  LOOP                         │────>│  SYNTHESIS    │────>│  SAVE    │\\n36: │              │     │  ┌─────────────────────────┐  │     │               │     │          │\\n37: │ Scope        │     │  │ Read State              │  │     │ Finding       │     │ Memory   │\\n38: │ Discovery    │     │  │ Check Convergence       │  │     │ Registry      │     │ Context  │\\n39: │ Dimension    │     │  │ Check Pause Sentinel    │  │     │ Dedup         │     │ Save     │\\n40: │ Ordering     │     │  │ Generate State Summary  │  │     │               │     │          │\\n41: │ Traceability │     │  │ Dispatch @deep-review   │  │     │ Severity      │     │          │\\n42: │ Planning     │     │  │ Evaluate Results        │  │     │ Reconcile     │     │          │\\n43: │ State Files  │     │  │ Claim Adjudication      │  │     │               │     │          │\\n44: │              │     │  │ Dashboard Generation    │  │     │ Replay        │     │          │\\n45: │              │     │  │ Loop Decision           │  │     │ Validation    │     │          │\\n46: │              │     │  └────────┬────────────────┘  │     │               │     │          │\\n47: │              │     │           │ repeat            │     │ review-report │     │          │\\n48: │              │     │           │                   │     │ (9 core +     │     │          │\\n49: │              │     │           │                   │     │  resource-map)│     │          │\\n50: └──────────────┘     └───────────────────────────────┘     └───────────────┘     └──────────┘\\n51: ```\\n52: \\n53: ### Core Innovation\\n54: \\n55: Each agent dispatch gets a fresh context window. State continuity comes from files on disk, not in-context memory. This eliminates context degradation in long review sessions where accumulated findings would otherwise bias subsequent dimensions.\\n56: \\n57: ### Key References\\n58: \\n59: | Resource | Path | Purpose |\\n60: |----------|------|---------|\\n61: | Review contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\\n62: | Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_auto.yaml` | Unattended review loop |\\n63: | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_confirm.yaml` | Step-by-step review with approval gates |\\n64: | Agent | `@deep-review` (LEAF) | Single iteration executor, no sub-agents, no WebFetch |\\n65: | Memory save | `generate-context.js` | Context preservation script |\\n66: \\n67: ---\\n68: \\n69: ## 2. PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\\n70: \\n71: ### Purpose\\n72: \\n73: Set up all state files for a new review session. Discover the scope, order dimensions by risk priority, establish the traceability protocol plan, and create the review state packet.\\n74: \\n75: ### Steps\\n76: \\n77: 1. **Classify session state before writing**:\\n78:    - `fresh`: no config/state/strategy files exist\\n79:    - `resume`: config + state + strategy all exist and agree\\n80:    - `completed-session`: consistent prior state with `config.status == \\\"complete\\\"`\\n81:    - `invalid-state`: partial or contradictory artifacts\\n82: \\n83: 2. **Resolve local artifact owner**: `artifact_dir = resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review').artifactDir`, then `mkdir -p {artifact_dir}/iterations`\\n84: \\n85: 3. **Scope discovery**: Resolve the review target into a concrete file list using one of 5 target types:\\n86: \\n87:    | Target Type | CLI Value | Resolution Strategy |\\n88:    |-------------|-----------|---------------------|\\n89:    | **Spec Folder** | `spec-folder` | Read `spec.md`, `plan.md`, implementation files listed in `tasks.md` |\\n90:    | **Skill** | `skill` | Read `SKILL.md`, `references/`, `assets/`, `scripts/`, find agent definitions and command entry points |\\n91:    | **Agent** | `agent` | Find agent definitions across all runtimes, compare for consistency |\\n92:    | **Track** | `track` | List all child spec folders under the track, read `spec.md` + `checklist.md` for each |\\n93:    | **Files** | `files` | Expand glob patterns, validate existence, discover cross-references |\\n94: \\n95:    Store the resolved file list in strategy.md \\\"Files Under Review\\\".\\n96: \\n97: 4. **Dimension ordering**: Order the 4 review dimensions for iteration based on risk priority:\\n98: \\n99:    | Priority | Dimension | Rationale |\\n100:    |----------|-----------|-----------|\\n101:    | 1 | Correctness | Logic errors have the highest blast radius |\\n102:    | 2 | Security | Vulnerabilities require immediate attention |\\n103:    | 3 | Traceability | Spec/code alignment ensures completeness |\\n104:    | 4 | Maintainability | Patterns and documentation quality (lowest immediate risk) |\\n105: \\n106:    Default order: D1 Correctness, D2 Security, D3 Traceability, D4 Maintainability. This order is configurable but the default prioritizes highest-impact dimensions first.\\n107: \\n108: 5. **Traceability protocol planning**: Partition the 6 cross-reference protocols into core vs overlay, and schedule only applicable overlays for the target type:\\n109: \\n110:    | Level | Protocol | Applies To | Gate Class | Purpose |\\n111:    |-------|----------|------------|------------|---------|\\n112:    | Core | `spec_code` | all targets | hard | Verify normative claims resolve to shipped behavior |\\n113:    | Core | `checklist_evidence` | all targets | hard | Verify checked completion claims have evidence |\\n114:    | Overlay | `skill_agent` | skill | advisory | Verify SKILL.md and runtime agents agree |\\n115:    | Overlay | `agent_cross_runtime` | agent | advisory | Verify runtime agent parity |\\n116:    | Overlay | `feature_catalog_code` | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory | Verify catalog claims match capability |\\n117:    | Overlay | `playbook_capability` | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory | Verify playbook scenarios match executable reality |\\n118: \\n119:    Only schedule overlay protocols that apply to the resolved target type.\\n120: \\n121: 6. **Write config**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` with `mode: \\\"review\\\"`, lineage metadata (`sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`), and review-specific fields including target, target type, dimensions, protocol plan, and release-readiness state.\\n122: \\n123: 7. **Initialize state log**: First line of `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` with config record including `mode: \\\"review\\\"` and the lineage fields.\\n124: \\n125: 8. **Initialize reducer state**: Create `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` with empty `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `repeatedFindings`, `dimensionCoverage`, `findingsBySeverity`, and `convergenceScore`.\\n126: \\n127: 9. **Initialize strategy**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` from review template with:\\n128:    - Topic (review target description)\\n129:    - Review Dimensions checklist\\n130:    - Files Under Review table\\n131:    - Cross-Reference Status table grouped by core vs overlay\\n132:    - Known Context from `memory_context()` results (if any)\\n133:    - Resource-map snapshot when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init\\n134:    - `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate` when it does not\\n135:    - Review Boundaries from config\\n136: 9a. **Initialize resource-map coverage state**:\\n137:    - If `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init: set `resource_map_present = true`, add `Resource Map Coverage` to the Review Charter, and persist a concise map summary in `Known Context`\\n138:    - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false`, record the skip note in `Known Context`, and continue without failing\\n139: \\n140: 10. **Validate review charter**:\\n141:    - Verify strategy.md contains Non-Goals and Stop Conditions sections (may be empty but must exist)\\n142:    - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (target, dimensions, scope, non-lned as the agent's context (native) or piped to `codex exec` stdin (cli-codex). Config is in `assets/deep_review_config.json` under the `executor` key; schema in `deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. CLI flag precedence: `--executor/--model/--reasoning-effort/--service-tier/--executor-timeout > config file > schema default`.\\n\\n### What Never Changes Regardless Of Executor Route\\n\\n- YAML owns state (`deep-review-state.jsonl`, strategy.md, registry, dashboard).\\n- `reduce-state.cjs` is the single state writer.\\n- Convergence detection, lifecycle events (new/resume/restart), the review dimensions pass, and stuck_recovery stay YAML-driven.\\n- The `@deep-review` LEAF agent definition is untouched: it is the native executor, not the only one.\\n\\n### Code-Graph Readiness TrustState Surface\\n\\nOn this skill surface, the live code-graph readiness contract only reaches four TrustState values: `live`, `stale`, `absent`, and `unavailable`. The values `cached`, `imported`, `rebuilt`, and `rehomed` remain declared in the shared TrustState type for compatibility and downstream schema stability, but the seven code-graph handlers and readiness helpers used here do not emit them today.\",\"lineStart\":1,\"lineEnd\":765,\"totalLines\":765,\"truncated\":false}},\"title\":\".opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\"time\":{\"start\":1781458394771,\"end\":1781458394774}},\"id\":\"prt_ec731de91001ef6FRPbOw4JGM0\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_138ce4b78ffe7H1eTmRgkr1Vek\",\"messageID\":\"msg_ec731d1a4001Z9oRMIzk5qL533\"}}\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/118-frontmatter-versioning/review/lineages/deepseek/logs/fanout-lineage.out:{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782210804719,\"sessionID\":\"ses_10bf585eeffeDIFj5xRNnSbPD5\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_01_AfUHgtnfqVMv9W8cErpu6411\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Deep Review Loop Protocol\\n3: description: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop, initialization, iteration, convergence, synthesis, and save phases.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"deep review loop protocol\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"review iteration lifecycle\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"review loop initialization\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"review auto resume\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"review synthesis phase\\\"\\n10: importance_tier: important\\n11: contextType: implementation\\n12: version: 1.11.0.29\\n13: ---\\n14: \\n15: # Deep Review Loop Protocol\\n16: \\n17: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop.\\n18: \\n19: ---\\n20: \\n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n22: \\n23: ### Purpose\\n24: \\n25: The deep review loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save. The YAML workflow manages the lifecycle. The `@deep-review` agent (LEAF-only, no WebFetch) executes individual review iterations with fresh context each time.\\n26: \\n27: ### When to Use\\n28: \\n29: - Initiating a deep-review loop on a spec folder, skill, agent, or track.\\n30: - Resuming a paused or interrupted review session from prior state.\\n31: - Validating the 4-phase lifecycle and lineage protocol against current behavior.\\n32: - Auditing iteration-dispatch, convergence, or save-phase contracts before changes.\\n33: \\n34: ```\\n35: ┌──────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\\n36: │  INIT        │────>│  LOOP                         │────>│  SYNTHESIS    │────>│  SAVE    │\\n37: │              │     │  ┌─────────────────────────┐  │     │               │     │          │\\n38: │ Scope        │     │  │ Read State              │  │     │ Finding       │     │ Memory   │\\n39: │ Discovery    │     │  │ Check Convergence       │  │     │ Registry      │     │ Context  │\\n40: │ Dimension    │     │  │ Check Pause Sentinel    │  │     │ Dedup         │     │ Save     │\\n41: │ Ordering     │     │  │ Generate State Summary  │  │     │               │     │          │\\n42: │ Traceability │     │  │ Dispatch @deep-review   │  │     │ Severity      │     │          │\\n43: │ Planning     │     │  │ Evaluate Results        │  │     │ Reconcile     │     │          │\\n44: │ State Files  │     │  │ Claim Adjudication      │  │     │               │     │          │\\n45: │              │     │  │ Dashboard Generation    │  │     │ Replay        │     │          │\\n46: │              │     │  │ Loop Decision           │  │     │ Validation    │     │          │\\n47: │              │     │  └────────┬────────────────┘  │     │               │     │          │\\n48: │              │     │           │ repeat            │     │ review-report │     │          │\\n49: │              │     │           │                   │     │ (9 core +     │     │          │\\n50: │              │     │           │                   │     │  resource-map)│     │          │\\n51: └──────────────┘     └───────────────────────────────┘     └───────────────┘     └──────────┘\\n52: ```\\n53: \\n54: ### Core Innovation\\n55: \\n56: Each agent dispatch gets a fresh context window. State continuity comes from files on disk, not in-context memory. This eliminates context degradation in long review sessions where accumulated findings would otherwise bias subsequent dimensions.\\n57: \\n58: ### Key References\\n59: \\n60: | Resource | Path | Purpose |\\n61: |----------|------|---------|\\n62: | Review contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\\n63: | Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` | Unattended review loop |\\n64: | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` | Step-by-step review with approval gates |\\n65: | Agent | `@deep-review` (LEAF) | Single iteration executor, no sub-agents, no WebFetch |\\n66: | Memory save | `generate-context.js` | Context preservation script |\\n67: \\n68: ---\\n69: \\n70: ## 2. PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\\n71: \\n72: ### Purpose\\n73: \\n74: Set up all state files for a new review session. Discover the scope, order dimensions by risk priority, establish the traceability protocol plan, and create the review state packet.\\n75: \\n76: ### Steps\\n77: \\n78: 1. **Classify session state before writing**:\\n79:    - `fresh`: no config/state/strategy files exist\\n80:    - `resume`: config + state + strategy all exist and agree\\n81:    - `completed-session`: consistent prior state with `config.status == \\\"complete\\\"`\\n82:    - `invalid-state`: partial or contradictory artifacts\\n83: \\n84: 2. **Resolve local artifact owner**: `artifact_dir = resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review').artifactDir`, then `mkdir -p {artifact_dir}/iterations`\\n85: \\n86: 3. **Scope discovery**: Resolve the review target into a concrete file list using one of 5 target types:\\n87: \\n88:    | Target Type | CLI Value | Resolution Strategy |\\n89:    |-------------|-----------|---------------------|\\n90:    | **Spec Folder** | `spec-folder` | Read `spec.md`, `plan.md`, implementation files listed in `tasks.md` |\\n91:    | **Skill** | `skill` | Read `SKILL.md`, `references/`, `assets/`, `scripts/`, find agent definitions and command entry points |\\n92:    | **Agent** | `agent` | Find agent definitions across all runtimes, compare for consistency |\\n93:    | **Track** | `track` | List all child spec folders under the track, read `spec.md` + `checklist.md` for each |\\n94:    | **Files** | `files` | Expand glob patterns, validate existence, discover cross-references |\\n95: \\n96:    Store the resolved file list in strategy.md \\\"Files Under Review\\\".\\n97: \\n98: 4. **Dimension ordering**: Order the 4 review dimensions for iteration based on risk priority:\\n99: \\n100:    | Priority | Dimension | Rationale |\\n101:    |----------|-----------|-----------|\\n102:    | 1 | Correctness | Logic errors have the highest blast radius |\\n103:    | 2 | Security | Vulnerabilities require immediate attention |\\n104:    | 3 | Traceability | Spec/code alignment ensures completeness |\\n105:    | 4 | Maintainability | Patterns and documentation quality (lowest immediate risk) |\\n106: \\n107:    Default order: D1 Correctness, D2 Security, D3 Traceability, D4 Maintainability. This order is configurable but the default prioritizes highest-impact dimensions first.\\n108: \\n109: 5. **Traceability protocol planning**: Partition the 6 cross-reference protocols into core vs overlay, and schedule only applicable overlays for the target type:\\n110: \\n111:    | Level | Protocol | Applies To | Gate Class | Purpose |\\n112:    |-------|----------|------------|------------|---------|\\n113:    | Core | `spec_code` | all targets | hard | Verify normative claims resolve to shipped behavior |\\n114:    | Core | `checklist_evidence` | all targets | hard | Verify checked completion claims have evidence |\\n115:    | Overlay | `skill_agent` | skill | advisory | Verify SKILL.md and runtime agents agree |\\n116:    | Overlay | `agent_cross_runtime` | agent | advisory | Verify runtime agent parity |\\n117:    | Overlay | `feature_catalog_code` | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory | Verify catalog claims match capability |\\n118:    | Overlay | `playbook_capability` | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory | Verify playbook scenarios match executable reality |\\n119: \\n120:    Only schedule overlay protocols that apply to the resolved target type.\\n121: \\n122: 6. **Write config**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` with `mode: \\\"review\\\"`, lineage metadata (`sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`), and review-specific fields including target, target type, dimensions, protocol plan, and release-readiness state.\\n123: \\n124: 7. **Initialize state log**: First line of `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` with config record including `mode: \\\"review\\\"` and the lineage fields.\\n125: \\n126: 8. **Initialize reducer state**: Create `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` with empty `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `repeatedFindings`, `dimensionCoverage`, `findingsBySeverity`, and `convergenceScore`.\\n127: \\n128: 9. **Initialize strategy**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` from review template with:\\n129:    - Topic (review target description)\\n130:    - Review Dimensions checklist\\n131:    - Files Under Review table\\n132:    - Cross-Reference Status table grouped by core vs overlay\\n133:    - Known Context from `memory_context()` results (if any)\\n134:    - Resource-map snapshot when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init\\n135:    - `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate` when it does not\\n136:    - Review Boundaries from config\\n137: 9a. **Initialize resource-map coverage state**:\\n138:    - If `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init: set `resource_map_present = true`, add `Resource Map Coverage` to the Review Charter, and persist a concise map summary in `Known Context`\\n139:    - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false`, record the skip note in `Known Context`, and continue without failing\\n140: \\n141: 10. **Validate review charter**:\\n142:    - Verify strategy.md contains Non-Goals and Stop Conditions sections (may be empty but must exist)\\n143:    - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (target, dimensions, scope, non-lned as the agent's context (native) or piped to `codex exec` stdin (cli-codex). Config is in `assets/deep_review_config.json` under the `executor` key; schema in `deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. CLI flag precedence: `--executor/--model/--reasoning-effort/--service-tier/--executor-timeout > config file > schema default`.\\n\\n### What Never Changes Regardless Of Executor Route\\n\\n- YAML owns state (`deep-review-state.jsonl`, strategy.md, registry, dashboard).\\n- `reduce-state.cjs` is the single state writer.\\n- Convergence detection, lifecycle events (new/resume/restart), the review dimensions pass, and stuck_recovery stay YAML-driven.\\n- The `@deep-review` LEAF agent definition is untouched: it is the native executor, not the only one.\\n\\n### Code-Graph Readiness TrustState Surface\\n\\nOn this skill surface, the live code-graph readiness contract only reaches four TrustState values: `live`, `stale`, `absent`, and `unavailable`. The values `cached`, `imported`, `rebuilt`, and `rehomed` remain declared in the shared TrustState type for compatibility and downstream schema stability, but the seven code-graph handlers and readiness helpers used here do not emit them today.\",\"lineStart\":1,\"lineEnd\":766,\"totalLines\":766,\"truncated\":false}},\"title\":\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\"time\":{\"start\":1782210804710,\"end\":1782210804715}},\"id\":\"prt_ef40aba4b001n2Ta9SZRe6YGiI\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_10bf585eeffeDIFj5xRNnSbPD5\",\"messageID\":\"msg_ef40aa9f4001zwwVGi7RCCeWFl\"}}\n.opencode/specs/design/002-mcp-open-design/review/session-audit/lineages/deepseek-v4-pro/logs/fanout-lineage.out:{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1781458398706,\"sessionID\":\"ses_138ce4b7fffegpX9L4tC4pzcvD\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_02_3Fei7oY9ODhmxt7ez1FK1351\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Deep Review Loop Protocol\\n3: description: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop, initialization, iteration, convergence, synthesis, and save phases.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"deep review loop protocol\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"review iteration lifecycle\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"review loop initialization\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"review auto resume\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"review synthesis phase\\\"\\n10: importance_tier: important\\n11: contextType: implementation\\n12: ---\\n13: \\n14: # Deep Review Loop Protocol\\n15: \\n16: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop.\\n17: \\n18: ---\\n19: \\n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n21: \\n22: ### Purpose\\n23: \\n24: The deep review loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save. The YAML workflow manages the lifecycle. The `@deep-review` agent (LEAF-only, no WebFetch) executes individual review iterations with fresh context each time.\\n25: \\n26: ### When to Use\\n27: \\n28: - Initiating a deep-review loop on a spec folder, skill, agent, or track.\\n29: - Resuming a paused or interrupted review session from prior state.\\n30: - Validating the 4-phase lifecycle and lineage protocol against current behavior.\\n31: - Auditing iteration-dispatch, convergence, or save-phase contracts before changes.\\n32: \\n33: ```\\n34: ┌──────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\\n35: │  INIT        │────>│  LOOP                         │────>│  SYNTHESIS    │────>│  SAVE    │\\n36: │              │     │  ┌─────────────────────────┐  │     │               │     │          │\\n37: │ Scope        │     │  │ Read State              │  │     │ Finding       │     │ Memory   │\\n38: │ Discovery    │     │  │ Check Convergence       │  │     │ Registry      │     │ Context  │\\n39: │ Dimension    │     │  │ Check Pause Sentinel    │  │     │ Dedup         │     │ Save     │\\n40: │ Ordering     │     │  │ Generate State Summary  │  │     │               │     │          │\\n41: │ Traceability │     │  │ Dispatch @deep-review   │  │     │ Severity      │     │          │\\n42: │ Planning     │     │  │ Evaluate Results        │  │     │ Reconcile     │     │          │\\n43: │ State Files  │     │  │ Claim Adjudication      │  │     │               │     │          │\\n44: │              │     │  │ Dashboard Generation    │  │     │ Replay        │     │          │\\n45: │              │     │  │ Loop Decision           │  │     │ Validation    │     │          │\\n46: │              │     │  └────────┬────────────────┘  │     │               │     │          │\\n47: │              │     │           │ repeat            │     │ review-report │     │          │\\n48: │              │     │           │                   │     │ (9 core +     │     │          │\\n49: │              │     │           │                   │     │  resource-map)│     │          │\\n50: └──────────────┘     └───────────────────────────────┘     └───────────────┘     └──────────┘\\n51: ```\\n52: \\n53: ### Core Innovation\\n54: \\n55: Each agent dispatch gets a fresh context window. State continuity comes from files on disk, not in-context memory. This eliminates context degradation in long review sessions where accumulated findings would otherwise bias subsequent dimensions.\\n56: \\n57: ### Key References\\n58: \\n59: | Resource | Path | Purpose |\\n60: |----------|------|---------|\\n61: | Review contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\\n62: | Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_auto.yaml` | Unattended review loop |\\n63: | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_confirm.yaml` | Step-by-step review with approval gates |\\n64: | Agent | `@deep-review` (LEAF) | Single iteration executor, no sub-agents, no WebFetch |\\n65: | Memory save | `generate-context.js` | Context preservation script |\\n66: \\n67: ---\\n68: \\n69: ## 2. PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\\n70: \\n71: ### Purpose\\n72: \\n73: Set up all state files for a new review session. Discover the scope, order dimensions by risk priority, establish the traceability protocol plan, and create the review state packet.\\n74: \\n75: ### Steps\\n76: \\n77: 1. **Classify session state before writing**:\\n78:    - `fresh`: no config/state/strategy files exist\\n79:    - `resume`: config + state + strategy all exist and agree\\n80:    - `completed-session`: consistent prior state with `config.status == \\\"complete\\\"`\\n81:    - `invalid-state`: partial or contradictory artifacts\\n82: \\n83: 2. **Resolve local artifact owner**: `artifact_dir = resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review').artifactDir`, then `mkdir -p {artifact_dir}/iterations`\\n84: \\n85: 3. **Scope discovery**: Resolve the review target into a concrete file list using one of 5 target types:\\n86: \\n87:    | Target Type | CLI Value | Resolution Strategy |\\n88:    |-------------|-----------|---------------------|\\n89:    | **Spec Folder** | `spec-folder` | Read `spec.md`, `plan.md`, implementation files listed in `tasks.md` |\\n90:    | **Skill** | `skill` | Read `SKILL.md`, `references/`, `assets/`, `scripts/`, find agent definitions and command entry points |\\n91:    | **Agent** | `agent` | Find agent definitions across all runtimes, compare for consistency |\\n92:    | **Track** | `track` | List all child spec folders under the track, read `spec.md` + `checklist.md` for each |\\n93:    | **Files** | `files` | Expand glob patterns, validate existence, discover cross-references |\\n94: \\n95:    Store the resolved file list in strategy.md \\\"Files Under Review\\\".\\n96: \\n97: 4. **Dimension ordering**: Order the 4 review dimensions for iteration based on risk priority:\\n98: \\n99:    | Priority | Dimension | Rationale |\\n100:    |----------|-----------|-----------|\\n101:    | 1 | Correctness | Logic errors have the highest blast radius |\\n102:    | 2 | Security | Vulnerabilities require immediate attention |\\n103:    | 3 | Traceability | Spec/code alignment ensures completeness |\\n104:    | 4 | Maintainability | Patterns and documentation quality (lowest immediate risk) |\\n105: \\n106:    Default order: D1 Correctness, D2 Security, D3 Traceability, D4 Maintainability. This order is configurable but the default prioritizes highest-impact dimensions first.\\n107: \\n108: 5. **Traceability protocol planning**: Partition the 6 cross-reference protocols into core vs overlay, and schedule only applicable overlays for the target type:\\n109: \\n110:    | Level | Protocol | Applies To | Gate Class | Purpose |\\n111:    |-------|----------|------------|------------|---------|\\n112:    | Core | `spec_code` | all targets | hard | Verify normative claims resolve to shipped behavior |\\n113:    | Core | `checklist_evidence` | all targets | hard | Verify checked completion claims have evidence |\\n114:    | Overlay | `skill_agent` | skill | advisory | Verify SKILL.md and runtime agents agree |\\n115:    | Overlay | `agent_cross_runtime` | agent | advisory | Verify runtime agent parity |\\n116:    | Overlay | `feature_catalog_code` | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory | Verify catalog claims match capability |\\n117:    | Overlay | `playbook_capability` | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory | Verify playbook scenarios match executable reality |\\n118: \\n119:    Only schedule overlay protocols that apply to the resolved target type.\\n120: \\n121: 6. **Write config**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` with `mode: \\\"review\\\"`, lineage metadata (`sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`), and review-specific fields including target, target type, dimensions, protocol plan, and release-readiness state.\\n122: \\n123: 7. **Initialize state log**: First line of `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` with config record including `mode: \\\"review\\\"` and the lineage fields.\\n124: \\n125: 8. **Initialize reducer state**: Create `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` with empty `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `repeatedFindings`, `dimensionCoverage`, `findingsBySeverity`, and `convergenceScore`.\\n126: \\n127: 9. **Initialize strategy**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` from review template with:\\n128:    - Topic (review target description)\\n129:    - Review Dimensions checklist\\n130:    - Files Under Review table\\n131:    - Cross-Reference Status table grouped by core vs overlay\\n132:    - Known Context from `memory_context()` results (if any)\\n133:    - Resource-map snapshot when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init\\n134:    - `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate` when it does not\\n135:    - Review Boundaries from config\\n136: 9a. **Initialize resource-map coverage state**:\\n137:    - If `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init: set `resource_map_present = true`, add `Resource Map Coverage` to the Review Charter, and persist a concise map summary in `Known Context`\\n138:    - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false`, record the skip note in `Known Context`, and continue without failing\\n139: \\n140: 10. **Validate review charter**:\\n141:    - Verify strategy.md contains Non-Goals and Stop Conditions sections (may be empty but must exist)\\n142:    - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (target, dimensions, scope, non-lned as the agent's context (native) or piped to `codex exec` stdin (cli-codex). Config is in `assets/deep_review_config.json` under the `executor` key; schema in `deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. CLI flag precedence: `--executor/--model/--reasoning-effort/--service-tier/--executor-timeout > config file > schema default`.\\n\\n### What Never Changes Regardless Of Executor Route\\n\\n- YAML owns state (`deep-review-state.jsonl`, strategy.md, registry, dashboard).\\n- `reduce-state.cjs` is the single state writer.\\n- Convergence detection, lifecycle events (new/resume/restart), the review dimensions pass, and stuck_recovery stay YAML-driven.\\n- The `@deep-review` LEAF agent definition is untouched: it is the native executor, not the only one.\\n\\n### Code-Graph Readiness TrustState Surface\\n\\nOn this skill surface, the live code-graph readiness contract only reaches four TrustState values: `live`, `stale`, `absent`, and `unavailable`. The values `cached`, `imported`, `rebuilt`, and `rehomed` remain declared in the shared TrustState type for compatibility and downstream schema stability, but the seven code-graph handlers and readiness helpers used here do not emit them today.\",\"lineStart\":1,\"lineEnd\":765,\"totalLines\":765,\"truncated\":false}},\"title\":\".opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\"time\":{\"start\":1781458398700,\"end\":1781458398704}},\"id\":\"prt_ec731ecc7001KkmyV0ITbbidwq\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_138ce4b7fffegpX9L4tC4pzcvD\",\"messageID\":\"msg_ec731db8c0018l2ak6fbsxJX6m\"}}\n\n=== orchestrate Deep Route Priority table ===\n95:### Agent Selection (Priority Order)\n97:| Priority | Task Type                                                                 | Agent                  | Tier | Skills                                                                            | subagent_type |\n116:| **LEAF**         | MUST NOT dispatch any sub-agents | @context, @code, @markdown, @ai-council, @review, @debug, @deep-research, @deep-review |\n206:├─ Agent: @code | @context | @markdown | @deep-context | @deep-research | @deep-review | @ai-council | @review | @debug\n207:├─ Deep Route: [for deep routes only: mode=<workflowMode>; target_agent=@<agent>; execution=<single_iteration|loop|session>; source_of_truth=.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json | none]\n840:- LEAF agents (@context, @general, @markdown, @ai-council, @review, @debug, @deep-research, @deep-review) execute work directly. If a LEAF agent spawns a sub-agent, it violates NDP. When dispatching LEAF agents, ALWAYS include the LEAF Enforcement Instruction (§2).\n","metadata":{"output":"...\n\n`spec.md`, `plan.md`, implementation files listed in `tasks.md` |\\n90:    | **Skill** | `skill` | Read `SKILL.md`, `references/`, `assets/`, `scripts/`, find agent definitions and command entry points |\\n91:    | **Agent** | `agent` | Find agent definitions across all runtimes, compare for consistency |\\n92:    | **Track** | `track` | List all child spec folders under the track, read `spec.md` + `checklist.md` for each |\\n93:    | **Files** | `files` | Expand glob patterns, validate existence, discover cross-references |\\n94: \\n95:    Store the resolved file list in strategy.md \\\"Files Under Review\\\".\\n96: \\n97: 4. **Dimension ordering**: Order the 4 review dimensions for iteration based on risk priority:\\n98: \\n99:    | Priority | Dimension | Rationale |\\n100:    |----------|-----------|-----------|\\n101:    | 1 | Correctness | Logic errors have the highest blast radius |\\n102:    | 2 | Security | Vulnerabilities require immediate attention |\\n103:    | 3 | Traceability | Spec/code alignment ensures completeness |\\n104:    | 4 | Maintainability | Patterns and documentation quality (lowest immediate risk) |\\n105: \\n106:    Default order: D1 Correctness, D2 Security, D3 Traceability, D4 Maintainability. This order is configurable but the default prioritizes highest-impact dimensions first.\\n107: \\n108: 5. **Traceability protocol planning**: Partition the 6 cross-reference protocols into core vs overlay, and schedule only applicable overlays for the target type:\\n109: \\n110:    | Level | Protocol | Applies To | Gate Class | Purpose |\\n111:    |-------|----------|------------|------------|---------|\\n112:    | Core | `spec_code` | all targets | hard | Verify normative claims resolve to shipped behavior |\\n113:    | Core | `checklist_evidence` | all targets | hard | Verify checked completion claims have evidence |\\n114:    | Overlay | `skill_agent` | skill | advisory | Verify SKILL.md and runtime agents agree |\\n115:    | Overlay | `agent_cross_runtime` | agent | advisory | Verify runtime agent parity |\\n116:    | Overlay | `feature_catalog_code` | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory | Verify catalog claims match capability |\\n117:    | Overlay | `playbook_capability` | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory | Verify playbook scenarios match executable reality |\\n118: \\n119:    Only schedule overlay protocols that apply to the resolved target type.\\n120: \\n121: 6. **Write config**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` with `mode: \\\"review\\\"`, lineage metadata (`sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`), and review-specific fields including target, target type, dimensions, protocol plan, and release-readiness state.\\n122: \\n123: 7. **Initialize state log**: First line of `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` with config record including `mode: \\\"review\\\"` and the lineage fields.\\n124: \\n125: 8. **Initialize reducer state**: Create `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` with empty `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `repeatedFindings`, `dimensionCoverage`, `findingsBySeverity`, and `convergenceScore`.\\n126: \\n127: 9. **Initialize strategy**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` from review template with:\\n128:    - Topic (review target description)\\n129:    - Review Dimensions checklist\\n130:    - Files Under Review table\\n131:    - Cross-Reference Status table grouped by core vs overlay\\n132:    - Known Context from `memory_context()` results (if any)\\n133:    - Resource-map snapshot when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init\\n134:    - `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate` when it does not\\n135:    - Review Boundaries from config\\n136: 9a. **Initialize resource-map coverage state**:\\n137:    - If `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init: set `resource_map_present = true`, add `Resource Map Coverage` to the Review Charter, and persist a concise map summary in `Known Context`\\n138:    - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false`, record the skip note in `Known Context`, and continue without failing\\n139: \\n140: 10. **Validate review charter**:\\n141:    - Verify strategy.md contains Non-Goals and Stop Conditions sections (may be empty but must exist)\\n142:    - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (target, dimensions, scope, non-lned as the agent's context (native) or piped to `codex exec` stdin (cli-codex). Config is in `assets/deep_review_config.json` under the `executor` key; schema in `deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. CLI flag precedence: `--executor/--model/--reasoning-effort/--service-tier/--executor-timeout > config file > schema default`.\\n\\n### What Never Changes Regardless Of Executor Route\\n\\n- YAML owns state (`deep-review-state.jsonl`, strategy.md, registry, dashboard).\\n- `reduce-state.cjs` is the single state writer.\\n- Convergence detection, lifecycle events (new/resume/restart), the review dimensions pass, and stuck_recovery stay YAML-driven.\\n- The `@deep-review` LEAF agent definition is untouched: it is the native executor, not the only one.\\n\\n### Code-Graph Readiness TrustState Surface\\n\\nOn this skill surface, the live code-graph readiness contract only reaches four TrustState values: `live`, `stale`, `absent`, and `unavailable`. The values `cached`, `imported`, `rebuilt`, and `rehomed` remain declared in the shared TrustState type for compatibility and downstream schema stability, but the seven code-graph handlers and readiness helpers used here do not emit them today.\",\"lineStart\":1,\"lineEnd\":765,\"totalLines\":765,\"truncated\":false}},\"title\":\".opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\"time\":{\"start\":1781458394771,\"end\":1781458394774}},\"id\":\"prt_ec731de91001ef6FRPbOw4JGM0\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_138ce4b78ffe7H1eTmRgkr1Vek\",\"messageID\":\"msg_ec731d1a4001Z9oRMIzk5qL533\"}}\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/118-frontmatter-versioning/review/lineages/deepseek/logs/fanout-lineage.out:{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782210804719,\"sessionID\":\"ses_10bf585eeffeDIFj5xRNnSbPD5\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_01_AfUHgtnfqVMv9W8cErpu6411\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Deep Review Loop Protocol\\n3: description: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop, initialization, iteration, convergence, synthesis, and save phases.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"deep review loop protocol\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"review iteration lifecycle\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"review loop initialization\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"review auto resume\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"review synthesis phase\\\"\\n10: importance_tier: important\\n11: contextType: implementation\\n12: version: 1.11.0.29\\n13: ---\\n14: \\n15: # Deep Review Loop Protocol\\n16: \\n17: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop.\\n18: \\n19: ---\\n20: \\n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n22: \\n23: ### Purpose\\n24: \\n25: The deep review loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save. The YAML workflow manages the lifecycle. The `@deep-review` agent (LEAF-only, no WebFetch) executes individual review iterations with fresh context each time.\\n26: \\n27: ### When to Use\\n28: \\n29: - Initiating a deep-review loop on a spec folder, skill, agent, or track.\\n30: - Resuming a paused or interrupted review session from prior state.\\n31: - Validating the 4-phase lifecycle and lineage protocol against current behavior.\\n32: - Auditing iteration-dispatch, convergence, or save-phase contracts before changes.\\n33: \\n34: ```\\n35: ┌──────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\\n36: │  INIT        │────>│  LOOP                         │────>│  SYNTHESIS    │────>│  SAVE    │\\n37: │              │     │  ┌─────────────────────────┐  │     │               │     │          │\\n38: │ Scope        │     │  │ Read State              │  │     │ Finding       │     │ Memory   │\\n39: │ Discovery    │     │  │ Check Convergence       │  │     │ Registry      │     │ Context  │\\n40: │ Dimension    │     │  │ Check Pause Sentinel    │  │     │ Dedup         │     │ Save     │\\n41: │ Ordering     │     │  │ Generate State Summary  │  │     │               │     │          │\\n42: │ Traceability │     │  │ Dispatch @deep-review   │  │     │ Severity      │     │          │\\n43: │ Planning     │     │  │ Evaluate Results        │  │     │ Reconcile     │     │          │\\n44: │ State Files  │     │  │ Claim Adjudication      │  │     │               │     │          │\\n45: │              │     │  │ Dashboard Generation    │  │     │ Replay        │     │          │\\n46: │              │     │  │ Loop Decision           │  │     │ Validation    │     │          │\\n47: │              │     │  └────────┬────────────────┘  │     │               │     │          │\\n48: │              │     │           │ repeat            │     │ review-report │     │          │\\n49: │              │     │           │                   │     │ (9 core +     │     │          │\\n50: │              │     │           │                   │     │  resource-map)│     │          │\\n51: └──────────────┘     └───────────────────────────────┘     └───────────────┘     └──────────┘\\n52: ```\\n53: \\n54: ### Core Innovation\\n55: \\n56: Each agent dispatch gets a fresh context window. State continuity comes from files on disk, not in-context memory. This eliminates context degradation in long review sessions where accumulated findings would otherwise bias subsequent dimensions.\\n57: \\n58: ### Key References\\n59: \\n60: | Resource | Path | Purpose |\\n61: |----------|------|---------|\\n62: | Review contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\\n63: | Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` | Unattended review loop |\\n64: | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` | Step-by-step review with approval gates |\\n65: | Agent | `@deep-review` (LEAF) | Single iteration executor, no sub-agents, no WebFetch |\\n66: | Memory save | `generate-context.js` | Context preservation script |\\n67: \\n68: ---\\n69: \\n70: ## 2. PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\\n71: \\n72: ### Purpose\\n73: \\n74: Set up all state files for a new review session. Discover the scope, order dimensions by risk priority, establish the traceability protocol plan, and create the review state packet.\\n75: \\n76: ### Steps\\n77: \\n78: 1. **Classify session state before writing**:\\n79:    - `fresh`: no config/state/strategy files exist\\n80:    - `resume`: config + state + strategy all exist and agree\\n81:    - `completed-session`: consistent prior state with `config.status == \\\"complete\\\"`\\n82:    - `invalid-state`: partial or contradictory artifacts\\n83: \\n84: 2. **Resolve local artifact owner**: `artifact_dir = resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review').artifactDir`, then `mkdir -p {artifact_dir}/iterations`\\n85: \\n86: 3. **Scope discovery**: Resolve the review target into a concrete file list using one of 5 target types:\\n87: \\n88:    | Target Type | CLI Value | Resolution Strategy |\\n89:    |-------------|-----------|---------------------|\\n90:    | **Spec Folder** | `spec-folder` | Read `spec.md`, `plan.md`, implementation files listed in `tasks.md` |\\n91:    | **Skill** | `skill` | Read `SKILL.md`, `references/`, `assets/`, `scripts/`, find agent definitions and command entry points |\\n92:    | **Agent** | `agent` | Find agent definitions across all runtimes, compare for consistency |\\n93:    | **Track** | `track` | List all child spec folders under the track, read `spec.md` + `checklist.md` for each |\\n94:    | **Files** | `files` | Expand glob patterns, validate existence, discover cross-references |\\n95: \\n96:    Store the resolved file list in strategy.md \\\"Files Under Review\\\".\\n97: \\n98: 4. **Dimension ordering**: Order the 4 review dimensions for iteration based on risk priority:\\n99: \\n100:    | Priority | Dimension | Rationale |\\n101:    |----------|-----------|-----------|\\n102:    | 1 | Correctness | Logic errors have the highest blast radius |\\n103:    | 2 | Security | Vulnerabilities require immediate attention |\\n104:    | 3 | Traceability | Spec/code alignment ensures completeness |\\n105:    | 4 | Maintainability | Patterns and documentation quality (lowest immediate risk) |\\n106: \\n107:    Default order: D1 Correctness, D2 Security, D3 Traceability, D4 Maintainability. This order is configurable but the default prioritizes highest-impact dimensions first.\\n108: \\n109: 5. **Traceability protocol planning**: Partition the 6 cross-reference protocols into core vs overlay, and schedule only applicable overlays for the target type:\\n110: \\n111:    | Level | Protocol | Applies To | Gate Class | Purpose |\\n112:    |-------|----------|------------|------------|---------|\\n113:    | Core | `spec_code` | all targets | hard | Verify normative claims resolve to shipped behavior |\\n114:    | Core | `checklist_evidence` | all targets | hard | Verify checked completion claims have evidence |\\n115:    | Overlay | `skill_agent` | skill | advisory | Verify SKILL.md and runtime agents agree |\\n116:    | Overlay | `agent_cross_runtime` | agent | advisory | Verify runtime agent parity |\\n117:    | Overlay | `feature_catalog_code` | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory | Verify catalog claims match capability |\\n118:    | Overlay | `playbook_capability` | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory | Verify playbook scenarios match executable reality |\\n119: \\n120:    Only schedule overlay protocols that apply to the resolved target type.\\n121: \\n122: 6. **Write config**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` with `mode: \\\"review\\\"`, lineage metadata (`sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`), and review-specific fields including target, target type, dimensions, protocol plan, and release-readiness state.\\n123: \\n124: 7. **Initialize state log**: First line of `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` with config record including `mode: \\\"review\\\"` and the lineage fields.\\n125: \\n126: 8. **Initialize reducer state**: Create `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` with empty `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `repeatedFindings`, `dimensionCoverage`, `findingsBySeverity`, and `convergenceScore`.\\n127: \\n128: 9. **Initialize strategy**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` from review template with:\\n129:    - Topic (review target description)\\n130:    - Review Dimensions checklist\\n131:    - Files Under Review table\\n132:    - Cross-Reference Status table grouped by core vs overlay\\n133:    - Known Context from `memory_context()` results (if any)\\n134:    - Resource-map snapshot when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init\\n135:    - `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate` when it does not\\n136:    - Review Boundaries from config\\n137: 9a. **Initialize resource-map coverage state**:\\n138:    - If `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init: set `resource_map_present = true`, add `Resource Map Coverage` to the Review Charter, and persist a concise map summary in `Known Context`\\n139:    - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false`, record the skip note in `Known Context`, and continue without failing\\n140: \\n141: 10. **Validate review charter**:\\n142:    - Verify strategy.md contains Non-Goals and Stop Conditions sections (may be empty but must exist)\\n143:    - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (target, dimensions, scope, non-lned as the agent's context (native) or piped to `codex exec` stdin (cli-codex). Config is in `assets/deep_review_config.json` under the `executor` key; schema in `deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. CLI flag precedence: `--executor/--model/--reasoning-effort/--service-tier/--executor-timeout > config file > schema default`.\\n\\n### What Never Changes Regardless Of Executor Route\\n\\n- YAML owns state (`deep-review-state.jsonl`, strategy.md, registry, dashboard).\\n- `reduce-state.cjs` is the single state writer.\\n- Convergence detection, lifecycle events (new/resume/restart), the review dimensions pass, and stuck_recovery stay YAML-driven.\\n- The `@deep-review` LEAF agent definition is untouched: it is the native executor, not the only one.\\n\\n### Code-Graph Readiness TrustState Surface\\n\\nOn this skill surface, the live code-graph readiness contract only reaches four TrustState values: `live`, `stale`, `absent`, and `unavailable`. The values `cached`, `imported`, `rebuilt`, and `rehomed` remain declared in the shared TrustState type for compatibility and downstream schema stability, but the seven code-graph handlers and readiness helpers used here do not emit them today.\",\"lineStart\":1,\"lineEnd\":766,\"totalLines\":766,\"truncated\":false}},\"title\":\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\"time\":{\"start\":1782210804710,\"end\":1782210804715}},\"id\":\"prt_ef40aba4b001n2Ta9SZRe6YGiI\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_10bf585eeffeDIFj5xRNnSbPD5\",\"messageID\":\"msg_ef40aa9f4001zwwVGi7RCCeWFl\"}}\n.opencode/specs/design/002-mcp-open-design/review/session-audit/lineages/deepseek-v4-pro/logs/fanout-lineage.out:{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1781458398706,\"sessionID\":\"ses_138ce4b7fffegpX9L4tC4pzcvD\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_02_3Fei7oY9ODhmxt7ez1FK1351\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Deep Review Loop Protocol\\n3: description: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop, initialization, iteration, convergence, synthesis, and save phases.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"deep review loop protocol\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"review iteration lifecycle\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"review loop initialization\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"review auto resume\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"review synthesis phase\\\"\\n10: importance_tier: important\\n11: contextType: implementation\\n12: ---\\n13: \\n14: # Deep Review Loop Protocol\\n15: \\n16: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop.\\n17: \\n18: ---\\n19: \\n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n21: \\n22: ### Purpose\\n23: \\n24: The deep review loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save. The YAML workflow manages the lifecycle. The `@deep-review` agent (LEAF-only, no WebFetch) executes individual review iterations with fresh context each time.\\n25: \\n26: ### When to Use\\n27: \\n28: - Initiating a deep-review loop on a spec folder, skill, agent, or track.\\n29: - Resuming a paused or interrupted review session from prior state.\\n30: - Validating the 4-phase lifecycle and lineage protocol against current behavior.\\n31: - Auditing iteration-dispatch, convergence, or save-phase contracts before changes.\\n32: \\n33: ```\\n34: ┌──────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\\n35: │  INIT        │────>│  LOOP                         │────>│  SYNTHESIS    │────>│  SAVE    │\\n36: │              │     │  ┌─────────────────────────┐  │     │               │     │          │\\n37: │ Scope        │     │  │ Read State              │  │     │ Finding       │     │ Memory   │\\n38: │ Discovery    │     │  │ Check Convergence       │  │     │ Registry      │     │ Context  │\\n39: │ Dimension    │     │  │ Check Pause Sentinel    │  │     │ Dedup         │     │ Save     │\\n40: │ Ordering     │     │  │ Generate State Summary  │  │     │               │     │          │\\n41: │ Traceability │     │  │ Dispatch @deep-review   │  │     │ Severity      │     │          │\\n42: │ Planning     │     │  │ Evaluate Results        │  │     │ Reconcile     │     │          │\\n43: │ State Files  │     │  │ Claim Adjudication      │  │     │               │     │          │\\n44: │              │     │  │ Dashboard Generation    │  │     │ Replay        │     │          │\\n45: │              │     │  │ Loop Decision           │  │     │ Validation    │     │          │\\n46: │              │     │  └────────┬────────────────┘  │     │               │     │          │\\n47: │              │     │           │ repeat            │     │ review-report │     │          │\\n48: │              │     │           │                   │     │ (9 core +     │     │          │\\n49: │              │     │           │                   │     │  resource-map)│     │          │\\n50: └──────────────┘     └───────────────────────────────┘     └───────────────┘     └──────────┘\\n51: ```\\n52: \\n53: ### Core Innovation\\n54: \\n55: Each agent dispatch gets a fresh context window. State continuity comes from files on disk, not in-context memory. This eliminates context degradation in long review sessions where accumulated findings would otherwise bias subsequent dimensions.\\n56: \\n57: ### Key References\\n58: \\n59: | Resource | Path | Purpose |\\n60: |----------|------|---------|\\n61: | Review contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\\n62: | Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_auto.yaml` | Unattended review loop |\\n63: | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_confirm.yaml` | Step-by-step review with approval gates |\\n64: | Agent | `@deep-review` (LEAF) | Single iteration executor, no sub-agents, no WebFetch |\\n65: | Memory save | `generate-context.js` | Context preservation script |\\n66: \\n67: ---\\n68: \\n69: ## 2. PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\\n70: \\n71: ### Purpose\\n72: \\n73: Set up all state files for a new review session. Discover the scope, order dimensions by risk priority, establish the traceability protocol plan, and create the review state packet.\\n74: \\n75: ### Steps\\n76: \\n77: 1. **Classify session state before writing**:\\n78:    - `fresh`: no config/state/strategy files exist\\n79:    - `resume`: config + state + strategy all exist and agree\\n80:    - `completed-session`: consistent prior state with `config.status == \\\"complete\\\"`\\n81:    - `invalid-state`: partial or contradictory artifacts\\n82: \\n83: 2. **Resolve local artifact owner**: `artifact_dir = resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review').artifactDir`, then `mkdir -p {artifact_dir}/iterations`\\n84: \\n85: 3. **Scope discovery**: Resolve the review target into a concrete file list using one of 5 target types:\\n86: \\n87:    | Target Type | CLI Value | Resolution Strategy |\\n88:    |-------------|-----------|---------------------|\\n89:    | **Spec Folder** | `spec-folder` | Read `spec.md`, `plan.md`, implementation files listed in `tasks.md` |\\n90:    | **Skill** | `skill` | Read `SKILL.md`, `references/`, `assets/`, `scripts/`, find agent definitions and command entry points |\\n91:    | **Agent** | `agent` | Find agent definitions across all runtimes, compare for consistency |\\n92:    | **Track** | `track` | List all child spec folders under the track, read `spec.md` + `checklist.md` for each |\\n93:    | **Files** | `files` | Expand glob patterns, validate existence, discover cross-references |\\n94: \\n95:    Store the resolved file list in strategy.md \\\"Files Under Review\\\".\\n96: \\n97: 4. **Dimension ordering**: Order the 4 review dimensions for iteration based on risk priority:\\n98: \\n99:    | Priority | Dimension | Rationale |\\n100:    |----------|-----------|-----------|\\n101:    | 1 | Correctness | Logic errors have the highest blast radius |\\n102:    | 2 | Security | Vulnerabilities require immediate attention |\\n103:    | 3 | Traceability | Spec/code alignment ensures completeness |\\n104:    | 4 | Maintainability | Patterns and documentation quality (lowest immediate risk) |\\n105: \\n106:    Default order: D1 Correctness, D2 Security, D3 Traceability, D4 Maintainability. This order is configurable but the default prioritizes highest-impact dimensions first.\\n107: \\n108: 5. **Traceability protocol planning**: Partition the 6 cross-reference protocols into core vs overlay, and schedule only applicable overlays for the target type:\\n109: \\n110:    | Level | Protocol | Applies To | Gate Class | Purpose |\\n111:    |-------|----------|------------|------------|---------|\\n112:    | Core | `spec_code` | all targets | hard | Verify normative claims resolve to shipped behavior |\\n113:    | Core | `checklist_evidence` | all targets | hard | Verify checked completion claims have evidence |\\n114:    | Overlay | `skill_agent` | skill | advisory | Verify SKILL.md and runtime agents agree |\\n115:    | Overlay | `agent_cross_runtime` | agent | advisory | Verify runtime agent parity |\\n116:    | Overlay | `feature_catalog_code` | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory | Verify catalog claims match capability |\\n117:    | Overlay | `playbook_capability` | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory | Verify playbook scenarios match executable reality |\\n118: \\n119:    Only schedule overlay protocols that apply to the resolved target type.\\n120: \\n121: 6. **Write config**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` with `mode: \\\"review\\\"`, lineage metadata (`sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`), and review-specific fields including target, target type, dimensions, protocol plan, and release-readiness state.\\n122: \\n123: 7. **Initialize state log**: First line of `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` with config record including `mode: \\\"review\\\"` and the lineage fields.\\n124: \\n125: 8. **Initialize reducer state**: Create `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` with empty `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `repeatedFindings`, `dimensionCoverage`, `findingsBySeverity`, and `convergenceScore`.\\n126: \\n127: 9. **Initialize strategy**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` from review template with:\\n128:    - Topic (review target description)\\n129:    - Review Dimensions checklist\\n130:    - Files Under Review table\\n131:    - Cross-Reference Status table grouped by core vs overlay\\n132:    - Known Context from `memory_context()` results (if any)\\n133:    - Resource-map snapshot when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init\\n134:    - `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate` when it does not\\n135:    - Review Boundaries from config\\n136: 9a. **Initialize resource-map coverage state**:\\n137:    - If `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init: set `resource_map_present = true`, add `Resource Map Coverage` to the Review Charter, and persist a concise map summary in `Known Context`\\n138:    - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false`, record the skip note in `Known Context`, and continue without failing\\n139: \\n140: 10. **Validate review charter**:\\n141:    - Verify strategy.md contains Non-Goals and Stop Conditions sections (may be empty but must exist)\\n142:    - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (target, dimensions, scope, non-lned as the agent's context (native) or piped to `codex exec` stdin (cli-codex). Config is in `assets/deep_review_config.json` under the `executor` key; schema in `deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. CLI flag precedence: `--executor/--model/--reasoning-effort/--service-tier/--executor-timeout > config file > schema default`.\\n\\n### What Never Changes Regardless Of Executor Route\\n\\n- YAML owns state (`deep-review-state.jsonl`, strategy.md, registry, dashboard).\\n- `reduce-state.cjs` is the single state writer.\\n- Convergence detection, lifecycle events (new/resume/restart), the review dimensions pass, and stuck_recovery stay YAML-driven.\\n- The `@deep-review` LEAF agent definition is untouched: it is the native executor, not the only one.\\n\\n### Code-Graph Readiness TrustState Surface\\n\\nOn this skill surface, the live code-graph readiness contract only reaches four TrustState values: `live`, `stale`, `absent`, and `unavailable`. The values `cached`, `imported`, `rebuilt`, and `rehomed` remain declared in the shared TrustState type for compatibility and downstream schema stability, but the seven code-graph handlers and readiness helpers used here do not emit them today.\",\"lineStart\":1,\"lineEnd\":765,\"totalLines\":765,\"truncated\":false}},\"title\":\".opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\"time\":{\"start\":1781458398700,\"end\":1781458398704}},\"id\":\"prt_ec731ecc7001KkmyV0ITbbidwq\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_138ce4b7fffegpX9L4tC4pzcvD\",\"messageID\":\"msg_ec731db8c0018l2ak6fbsxJX6m\"}}\n\n=== orchestrate Deep Route Priority table ===\n95:### Agent Selection (Priority Order)\n97:| Priority | Task Type                                                                 | Agent                  | Tier | Skills                                                                            | subagent_type |\n116:| **LEAF**         | MUST NOT dispatch any sub-agents | @context, @code, @markdown, @ai-council, @review, @debug, @deep-research, @deep-review |\n206:├─ Agent: @code | @context | @markdown | @deep-context | @deep-research | @deep-review | @ai-council | @review | @debug\n207:├─ Deep Route: [for deep routes only: mode=<workflowMode>; target_agent=@<agent>; execution=<single_iteration|loop|session>; source_of_truth=.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json | none]\n840:- LEAF agents (@context, @general, @markdown, @ai-council, @review, @debug, @deep-research, @deep-review) execute work directly. If a LEAF agent spawns a sub-agent, it violates NDP. When dispatching LEAF agents, ALWAYS include the LEAF Enforcement Instruction (§2).\n","exit":0,"truncated":true,"outputPath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/.local/share/opencode/tool-output/tool_f1c63bf02001LdLiNirEJQJPzL"},"title":"cd \"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public\" && echo \"=== self-invocation guard (OPENCODE_PID) ===\"; rg -rn \"OPENCODE_PID|self.invocation|self_invocation|nested.*opencode|refused from inside\" .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/ 2>/dev/null | head -15; echo \"\"; echo \"=== mk-goal plugin / injection pattern (032) ===\"; rg -rln \"mk-goal|injection.plugin|hook.*inject|goal.*inject\" .opencode/specs/ 2>/dev/null | head -10; echo \"\"; echo \"=== orchestrate Deep Route Priority table ===\"; rg -n \"Deep Route|Priority|deep-context|deep-review\" .opencode/agents/orchestrate.md | head -20","time":{"start":1782887726854,"end":1782887726865}},"id":"prt_f1c63becd001h5uEW20EXYj7wo","sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbd6ffex3B3McvCZaMchj","messageID":"msg_f1c6379be001T3rJNLG7Ho84IW"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1782887727491,"sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbd6ffex3B3McvCZaMchj","part":{"id":"prt_f1c63c17e001RL2NwV8SfvJdng","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"6d9a7e5dacbf04e2a0140385843ff24f912f6687","messageID":"msg_f1c6379be001T3rJNLG7Ho84IW","sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbd6ffex3B3McvCZaMchj","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":125188,"input":2547,"output":216,"reasoning":121,"cache":{"write":0,"read":122304}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1782887743707,"sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbd6ffex3B3McvCZaMchj","part":{"id":"prt_f1c6400d700165z2SeaP2kdAtJ","messageID":"msg_f1c63c33a001vU4o3Q35y9KtyM","sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbd6ffex3B3McvCZaMchj","snapshot":"6d9a7e5dacbf04e2a0140385843ff24f912f6687","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1782887752782,"sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbd6ffex3B3McvCZaMchj","part":{"id":"prt_f1c6424480015tw2Gs1uDXqQzO","messageID":"msg_f1c63c33a001vU4o3Q35y9KtyM","sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbd6ffex3B3McvCZaMchj","type":"text","text":"Let me get the precise self-invocation guard citation and the plugin pattern from packet 032 with tighter grep scoping.","time":{"start":1782887752776,"end":1782887752781}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782887752813,"sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbd6ffex3B3McvCZaMchj","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_1833a2ba62c347f8a7a9994d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"cd \"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public\" && echo \"=== cli-opencode self-invocation guard ===\"; rg -n \"OPENCODE_PID|self.invocation|refused from inside|nested\" .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md 2>/dev/null | head; echo \"=== packet 032 plugin/injection ===\"; ls .opencode/specs/ | rg \"032|033|plugin|goal|inject\" 2>/dev/null | head; echo \"=== goal-prompt ===\"; head -40 \".opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/goal-prompt.md\" 2>/dev/null"},"output":"=== cli-opencode self-invocation guard ===\n16:> A running CLI skill never dispatches itself. The cli-X skills are for **cross-AI delegation only** — never self-invocation.\n66:def detect_self_invocation():\n87:if detect_self_invocation():\n142:    \"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\": [\"full reference\", \"all templates\", \"deep dive\", \"complete guide\", \"opencode agent\", \"opencode prompt\", \"share url\", \"ablation\", \"worker farm\", \"self-invocation\", \"memory handback\", \"minimax\", \"MiniMax-M3\", \"tidd-ec\"],\n310:Install missing binaries, refuse ambiguous self-invocation, run provider pre-flight for model/auth errors, check version drift for unknown flags, force `--format json` for empty streams, add `</dev/null` for background loops, confirm `--share`, use `--pure` only for plugin crashes, and inspect state logs for stuck sessions.\n319:2. **Run the self-invocation guard before dispatch** (ADR-001): Layer 1 env-var lookup for any `OPENCODE_*`, Layer 2 process-ancestry probe for `opencode` parent, Layer 3 `~/.opencode/state/<id>/lock` probe. Trip on ANY positive — refuse unless prompt has explicit parallel-session keywords.\n375:- [integration_patterns.md](./references/integration_patterns.md) - 3 use cases, decision tree, self-invocation guard, silent stdin\n=== packet 032 plugin/injection ===\n=== goal-prompt ===\n# GOAL PROMPT — GPT-Backed OpenCode Deep-Loop Reliability (Packet 031)\n\n**OBJECTIVE.** Make GPT-backed OpenCode (GPT-5.5 high/fast) reliably invoke and execute deep-loop workflows (deep-research, deep-review, deep-context, deep-ai-council) the way Claude Sonnet/Opus does — correctly, promptly, without getting stuck on pre-defined flows or over-literal misreads — and determine what packet 031 still needs to prove or build to get there.\n\n**SPEC FOLDER (Gate 3, established):** `.opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/`\n\n**OBSERVED SYMPTOMS (operator report, 2026-07-01, real-world OpenCode usage).** GPT is very slow as `@orchestrate` primary agent. GPT frequently fails to invoke the correct deep sub-agent (deep-research/-review/-context/-ai-council) even after phases 001-004 landed. GPT gets stuck on pre-defined flows, especially deep-loop commands, possibly others too. GPT overthinks and needs literal, deterministic instructions rather than prose/judgment.\n\n**WHAT 031 ALREADY ESTABLISHED (do not re-derive).** Root cause: `subagent_type` is normalized to `\"general\"` for every custom-agent dispatch — specialized identity is only prompt-injected, never runtime-enforced (a soft identity boundary). Phases 001-004 (route-proof validation, `deep.md` primary router, `orchestrate.md` Deep Route field, pre-route headers) are code-complete and independently re-verified. Phase 005 (GPT verification smoke, the acceptance gate) is **inconclusive, not a clean pass**: 0/4 command-owned smokes reached a real leaf dispatch — all blocked upstream by `cli-opencode` self-invocation guards before actual routing behavior could be observed. `graph-metadata.json` wrongly reports it \"complete\" while every prose doc says \"Failed/blocked, not accepted.\" Phase 006 (host-hard-identity/FIX-5) stays Parked on that inconclusive evidence, not on proof the agent-layer fix works. `deep.md` (`mode: primary`, deterministic table lookup) is materially more literal-model-safe than `orchestrate.md`'s Deep Route field, which requires GPT to self-derive `mode=`/`execution=` — a plausible source of the overthinking/stuck-flow symptom. `ai-council` is currently `mode: all` (directly invocable), not subagent-only. Systemic graph-metadata drift across the packet (parent/child paths pointing at nonexistent folders) needs cleanup.\n\n**NEW DIRECTIONS TO INVESTIGATE/DESIGN.** (1) Convert `ai-council` to subagent-only, or justify keeping dual-reachability. (2) Harden `@orchestrate` so deep-loop dispatch is table-lookup-deterministic for GPT, matching `deep.md`. (3) Propagate hardening to affected commands/skills beyond orchestrate/deep.md. (4) Evaluate an OpenCode plugin (candidate home: `system-skill-advisor`) that structurally enforces correct sub-agent selection instead of relying on prompt discipline. (5) Design a GPT-vs-Claude behavioral benchmark (latency + first-dispatch correctness) to run alongside future deep-research. (6) Resolve whether 006/FIX-5 should actually unpark given real-world evidence now corroborates the inconclusive smoke result.\n\n**METHOD / SEQUENCE.** (1) Update 031's root `spec.md` + affected phase docs/JSONs to capture the symptoms and directions above, and fix the graph-metadata drift. (2) Run `/deep:research` for ≥30 iterations — GLM-5.2 max-thinking + GPT-5.5 high-fast lineages, anti-convergence floor forced to the full iteration count so it does not stop early — actively pivoting angles as it deepens rather than settling on the first plausible design. (3) Synthesize findings into an expanded/upgraded 031 phased plan (new and/or revised phases) with concrete, evidence-backed recommendations.\n\n**DISCIPLINE.** Distinguish confirmed (file:line evidence) from inferred throughout. Do not let the research loop converge on \"phases 001-004 are enough\" without addressing why phase 005's smoke never reached a real leaf dispatch — that gap is the crux, not a footnote.\n","metadata":{"output":"=== cli-opencode self-invocation guard ===\n16:> A running CLI skill never dispatches itself. The cli-X skills are for **cross-AI delegation only** — never self-invocation.\n66:def detect_self_invocation():\n87:if detect_self_invocation():\n142:    \"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\": [\"full reference\", \"all templates\", \"deep dive\", \"complete guide\", \"opencode agent\", \"opencode prompt\", \"share url\", \"ablation\", \"worker farm\", \"self-invocation\", \"memory handback\", \"minimax\", \"MiniMax-M3\", \"tidd-ec\"],\n310:Install missing binaries, refuse ambiguous self-invocation, run provider pre-flight for model/auth errors, check version drift for unknown flags, force `--format json` for empty streams, add `</dev/null` for background loops, confirm `--share`, use `--pure` only for plugin crashes, and inspect state logs for stuck sessions.\n319:2. **Run the self-invocation guard before dispatch** (ADR-001): Layer 1 env-var lookup for any `OPENCODE_*`, Layer 2 process-ancestry probe for `opencode` parent, Layer 3 `~/.opencode/state/<id>/lock` probe. Trip on ANY positive — refuse unless prompt has explicit parallel-session keywords.\n375:- [integration_patterns.md](./references/integration_patterns.md) - 3 use cases, decision tree, self-invocation guard, silent stdin\n=== packet 032 plugin/injection ===\n=== goal-prompt ===\n# GOAL PROMPT — GPT-Backed OpenCode Deep-Loop Reliability (Packet 031)\n\n**OBJECTIVE.** Make GPT-backed OpenCode (GPT-5.5 high/fast) reliably invoke and execute deep-loop workflows (deep-research, deep-review, deep-context, deep-ai-council) the way Claude Sonnet/Opus does — correctly, promptly, without getting stuck on pre-defined flows or over-literal misreads — and determine what packet 031 still needs to prove or build to get there.\n\n**SPEC FOLDER (Gate 3, established):** `.opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/`\n\n**OBSERVED SYMPTOMS (operator report, 2026-07-01, real-world OpenCode usage).** GPT is very slow as `@orchestrate` primary agent. GPT frequently fails to invoke the correct deep sub-agent (deep-research/-review/-context/-ai-council) even after phases 001-004 landed. GPT gets stuck on pre-defined flows, especially deep-loop commands, possibly others too. GPT overthinks and needs literal, deterministic instructions rather than prose/judgment.\n\n**WHAT 031 ALREADY ESTABLISHED (do not re-derive).** Root cause: `subagent_type` is normalized to `\"general\"` for every custom-agent dispatch — specialized identity is only prompt-injected, never runtime-enforced (a soft identity boundary). Phases 001-004 (route-proof validation, `deep.md` primary router, `orchestrate.md` Deep Route field, pre-route headers) are code-complete and independently re-verified. Phase 005 (GPT verification smoke, the acceptance gate) is **inconclusive, not a clean pass**: 0/4 command-owned smokes reached a real leaf dispatch — all blocked upstream by `cli-opencode` self-invocation guards before actual routing behavior could be observed. `graph-metadata.json` wrongly reports it \"complete\" while every prose doc says \"Failed/blocked, not accepted.\" Phase 006 (host-hard-identity/FIX-5) stays Parked on that inconclusive evidence, not on proof the agent-layer fix works. `deep.md` (`mode: primary`, deterministic table lookup) is materially more literal-model-safe than `orchestrate.md`'s Deep Route field, which requires GPT to self-derive `mode=`/`execution=` — a plausible source of the overthinking/stuck-flow symptom. `ai-council` is currently `mode: all` (directly invocable), not subagent-only. Systemic graph-metadata drift across the packet (parent/child paths pointing at nonexistent folders) needs cleanup.\n\n**NEW DIRECTIONS TO INVESTIGATE/DESIGN.** (1) Convert `ai-council` to subagent-only, or justify keeping dual-reachability. (2) Harden `@orchestrate` so deep-loop dispatch is table-lookup-deterministic for GPT, matching `deep.md`. (3) Propagate hardening to affected commands/skills beyond orchestrate/deep.md. (4) Evaluate an OpenCode plugin (candidate home: `system-skill-advisor`) that structurally enforces correct sub-agent selection instead of relying on prompt discipline. (5) Design a GPT-vs-Claude behavioral benchmark (latency + first-dispatch correctness) to run alongside future deep-research. (6) Resolve whether 006/FIX-5 should actually unpark given real-world evidence now corroborates the inconclusive smoke result.\n\n**METHOD / SEQUENCE.** (1) Update 031's root `spec.md` + affected phase docs/JSONs to capture the symptoms and directions above, and fix the graph-metadata drift. (2) Run `/deep:research` for ≥30 iterations — GLM-5.2 max-thinking + GPT-5.5 high-fast lineages, anti-convergence floor forced to the full iteration count so it does not stop early — actively pivoting angles as it deepens rather than settling on the first plausible design. (3) Synthesize findings into an expanded/upgraded 031 phased plan (new and/or revised phases) with concrete, evidence-backed recommendations.\n\n**DISCIPLINE.** Distinguish confirmed (file:line evidence) from inferred throughout. Do not let the research loop converge on \"phases 001-004 are enough\" without addressing why phase 005's smoke never reached a real leaf dispatch — that gap is the crux, not a footnote.\n","exit":0,"truncated":false},"title":"cd \"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public\" && echo \"=== cli-opencode self-invocation guard ===\"; rg -n \"OPENCODE_PID|self.invocation|refused from inside|nested\" .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md 2>/dev/null | head; echo \"=== packet 032 plugin/injection ===\"; ls .opencode/specs/ | rg \"032|033|plugin|goal|inject\" 2>/dev/null | head; echo \"=== goal-prompt ===\"; head -40 \".opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/goal-prompt.md\" 2>/dev/null","time":{"start":1782887752811,"end":1782887752812}},"id":"prt_f1c64244a00172Q2anUEZxTWh