{"type":"text","timestamp":1782887794125,"sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbd6ffex3B3McvCZaMchj","part":{"id":"prt_f1c64b4e4001RdijgRFyr0kPh1","messageID":"msg_f1c64282c001b0O1IEFPVDwBgj","sessionID":"ses_0e3a7cbd6ffex3B3McvCZaMchj","type":"text","text":"I now have all the precise evidence citations needed. The self-invocation guard is a 3-layer detector (any `OPENCODE_*` env var, opencode in process ancestry, or a state lock) at `cli-opencode/SKILL.md:66,87,319`.\n\nphase_init is done. Now I'll build **phase_main_loop** — 30 evidence-grounded iterations. I'll write a lineage driver script (within the allowed lineage path) that generates the iteration files, JSONL log, reducer outputs, and synthesis. Let me first write the iteration data + writer covering iterations 1-15.","time":{"start":1782887789796,"end":1782887794123}}}
